-- Former British Airways CEO Colin Marshall Dies, Times Reports
-- B y   K a r i   L u n d g r e n
-- 2012-07-07T07:49:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-07/former-british-airways-ceo-colin-marshall-dies-times-reports.html
Colin Marshall, a former chief
executive officer of British Airways Plc and ex-president of the
 Confederation of British Industry , has died, the Times reported.  Marshall, who was 78, led British Airways for 13 years
prior to the company’s privatization in 1987, the London
newspaper said. Marshall had also served on the board of  HSBC
Holdings Plc (HSBA)  and as chairman of  Invensys Plc (ISYS)  and  Inchcape Plc. (INCH)   He was made a peer in the House of Lords in 1998 and had
the title Lord Marshall of Knightsbridge, according to the U.K.
Parliament’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kari Lundgren in London at 
